## Padrão Bronze — leitura e escrita

```python
# Leitura do Kafka
df = spark.readStream \
    .format("kafka") \
    .option("kafka.bootstrap.servers", kafka_bootstrap) \
    .option("subscribe", kafka_topic) \
    .option("startingOffsets", starting_offsets) \
    .option("maxOffsetsPerTrigger", int(max_offsets)) \
    .load()

# Parse Avro com Schema Registry
from pyspark.sql.functions import from_avro
parsed = df.select(
    from_avro(col("value"),
              options={"schemaRegistryAddress": schema_registry_url}
             ).alias("data"),
    col("offset").alias("_kafka_offset"),
    col("timestamp").alias("_kafka_timestamp")
)

# Escrita append-only
parsed.writeStream \
    .format("delta") \
    .outputMode("append") \
    .option("checkpointLocation", checkpoint_path) \
    .trigger(availableNow=True) \
    .toTable(bronze_table)
```

## Padrão Silver — MERGE INTO

```python
def merge_to_silver(df_batch, batch_id):
    df_batch = df_batch.withColumn("_processed_at", current_timestamp())
    df_batch.createOrReplaceTempView("staging_silver")
    spark.sql(f"""
        MERGE INTO {silver_table} AS target
        USING staging_silver AS source
        ON target.{merge_key} = source.{merge_key}
        WHEN MATCHED AND source.__source_ts_ms > target.__source_ts_ms
            THEN UPDATE SET *
        WHEN NOT MATCHED
            THEN INSERT *
    """)

df.writeStream \
    .foreachBatch(merge_to_silver) \
    .option("checkpointLocation", checkpoint_path) \
    .trigger(availableNow=True) \
    .start()
```

## Campos especiais do Debezium (pós-SMT)

Os registros chegam flat com dois campos adicionados pelo SMT:
- `__op` — tipo de operação: `c` (insert), `u` (update), `r` (snapshot), `d` (delete)
- `__source_ts_ms` — timestamp do evento no PostgreSQL em milissegundos

## JSONB fields — payment_events e order_status

```python
from pyspark.sql.functions import get_json_object

# payment_events.event é JSONB → chega como string
df = df.withColumn("event_name",
    get_json_object(col("data.event"), "$.event_name"))
df = df.withColumn("event_ts",
    get_json_object(col("data.event"), "$.timestamp").cast("long"))
```

## Regras anti-pattern

| Nunca fazer | Por quê | Em vez disso |
|---|---|---|
| Ler Bronze em notebooks Gold | Viola lineage Medallion | Sempre ler Silver |
| Hardcodar catalog name | Quebra dev/prod parity | Widget + DABs variable |
| `trigger(continuous=True)` | Cluster sempre ligado | `trigger(availableNow=True)` |
| cluster_by ≠ merge_key | Full table scan no MERGE | Alinhar (ADR-04) |
